    def save_cmds(cmds, filename='cmds.tao'): # Write to file for running with vanilla Tao
    with open(filename, 'w') as f:
        f.write('set global lattice_calc_on = F\n')
        f.write('set global plot_on = F\n')    
        for cmd in CMDS:
            f.write(cmd+'\n')
        f.write('set global lattice_calc_on = T\n')        
        f.write('set global plot_on = T\n')
    def save_cmds(cmds, filename='cmds.tao'): # Write to file for running with vanilla Tao with open(filename, 'w') as f: f.write('set global lattice_calc_on = F\n') f.write('set global plot_on = F\n') for cmd in CMDS: f.write(cmd+'\n') f.write('set global lattice_calc_on = T\n') f.write('set global plot_on = T\n')
